TWO drug dealers were arrested on Tuesday by officers patrolling in Eden Park, Ekurhuleni. Ekurhuleni Metro police acting spokesman Kobeli Mokheseng said: “Just before 2pm, members of the drug enforcement unit arrested a 42-year-old man and a 32-year-old woman found in possession of khat. “Officers who were patrolling the area were approached by a concerned resident about a house in Leyland Street where drug dealing was allegedly the order of the day. “The building was raided and the couple was found with 150 bags of khat with a estimated street value of R15 000. “It is not the first time the two were arrested for this offence. “They were locked up at Eden Park Police Station for drug possession and dealing in illicit substances.” The two suspects are expected to appear in Palm Ridge Magistrates Court soon.